<para0 verstatus="ver" security="u"><title>Use of "Shall", "Will",
"Should", and "May"</title>
<para>The word "shall" is used to express a provision that is binding.
 The words "should" and "may" are used when it is necessary to express
non-mandatory provisions.  The word "will" may be used to express
a mandatory declaration of purpose or when it is necessary to express
a future event.</para>
</para0>
<applicdef verstatus="ver"><title>List of Applicability and Effectivity</title>
<para>In this example the &ldquo;TERM&rdquo; heading is used to define
the column used for the symbol. The &ldquo;DEFINITION&rdquo; heading
is used to define the applicability/effectivity for the symbol used
in the &ldquo;TERM&rdquo; column.</para>
